      <heading>Sun Mar 19 (Lethan)     :: Caemlyn : That Shadow Tainted City!!!</heading>
      <slot>3</slot>
      <level>184</level>
      <author>0</author>
      <date>0</date>
      <text>In the Light,
   On my patrols in Caemlyn I came across a foul group of people....a full half dozen of them who proceeded to verablly abuse and accost me for no apparent reason. I proceeded to question them closely, it was my intention to ascertain whether they walked the path of the light and were misguided mayhap, or whether they had fallen into the shadow.

   I was ATTACKED! These fools attacked me, a true Child of the Light in the middle of Caemlyn. When it almost came to a fully fledged sword fight, the Queen's Guard's finally came along and they surrounded us all.

   I rejoiced, because while the Queen's Guard's have oft-times in the past seemed critical of us, the Children of the Light, they have always abhored any violence in their city.

   So what did the shadow tainted fools do?! They proceeded to allow those half-dozen men and women to go FREE! AND THEN THEY GROUPED UP AND SURROUNDED _ME_!!! DECLARING ME THE ANTAGONIST OF THE ENTIRE SITUATION!

   I quite rightfully expressed my most vocal and adamant denial of that accusation and then they proceeded to advance upon me, murder in their shadow tainted gaze. Caemlyners looked on in fear as they watched the Queen's Guard's attack me for nothing, until another of my squad stationed in Caemlyn *desc unamed*, came to my aid.

   At that point we reacted in unison and I took two of those foul miscreants out with two fell swipes of my light guided sword before taking a third in the chest. Two more that were arrayed against me attacked and I moved, relieving them of their knee caps.

   Only the first two were mortally wounded while my compatriot battled against another volley of guards who had hesitated to their err between returning to attack me again and meeting him. One more fell to a hamstring from my squad man before we fleed these obvious darkfriends presence for surely the sounds of approaching reinforcements was ringing foully in the air.

In the light, always,
  Lethan Mosen.

*descs of Rhyne, Archelin, Ryokui, Stephen, Rhayn, Tenebrius supplied dutifully*
</text>
