      <heading>Tue Sep 12 (Kazin)      :: Sayings Volume 2 (look back at #7)</heading>
      <slot>6</slot>
      <level>32</level>
      <author>0</author>
      <date>0</date>
      <text>The Children of the Light are at war with forces too
terrible to comprehend.  We cannot afford mercy for
any of its victims too weak to take the morally correct
course.  Mercy destroys us, it weakens us, and saps
our resolve.  Put aside all such thoughts.  They are
not worthy of Soldiers in the service of the Light.
Praise the Creator for in our resolve we reflect His
purpose of will.

Protestations of Innocence Prove Nothing.

The weak will always be lead by the strong.  Where the
strong see purpose and act, the weak follow.  Where
the strong cry out against the Pattern of the Wheel,
the weak bow their heads and succomb.  There are many
who are weak, and many are their temptations.  Despise
the weak for they flock to the call of the Shadow.  Pity
them not and scorn their cries of innocence- it is
better that one hundred innocents fall before the swords
of the Light than one kneel before the Dark One.

Victory needs no explaination.  Defeat allows none.

Huddle close to your False Dragon if he makes you feel
safe.  He cannot save you, for only the Light is eternal.

For Questioners only:
  Why struggle?  Your soul will feel so much better when
we're finished.

Also for Questioners only:
  I am not asking for your blood.  I can -take- your
blood.  I am asking for your soul.  Only you can return
your soul to the Light.

For those losing fights:
  The dark tide of Shadowspawn is upon us, and we are
alone.  There can be no mercy, no surrender.  If we
survive this day it will be a miracle.

There can be no bystanders in the battle against the
Shadow.  Anyone who will not fight by our side is an
enemy to be crushed.

Want more?  Let me know.  I'm only about halfway through.
-Kazin.
</text>
    </message>
