      <author>0</author>
      <date>0</date>
      <text> The Prophet and his mobs are at it again!  They push across our northern
 border and burn everything they come close to!  They are a seething mass
 of Lightforsaken Darkfriends all!  Our soldiers seem to have no success in
 pushing them back across into Ghealdan, but luckily, they seem more intent
 on looting and burning the outlying villages than actually pressing a full advance
 into the heart of Amadicia, to Amador itself.  But this can't last, this foul
 Prophet must be stopped, purged from our blessed lands, before he can spread
 his lies and chaos further.  Something must be done, our troops seem to only
 have success in distracting them, much less defeating them.  If the opinion
 of a low ranking individual, such as myself, were valued, I'd venture it's time
 we stop treating the Prophet as a joke, and more like a genuine threat to Amadicia!
 
 Sergeant Cayhill
 
 (posted during a brief stay at the Fortress of the Light, while re-supplying before
 returning to the northern border of Amadicia)
 
