      <heading>Sat Feb 16 (Arif)       :: &amp;bA note to the Officers&amp;n</heading>
      <slot>9</slot>
      <level>161</level>
      <author>0</author>
      <date>0</date>
      <text>While returning from delivering dispatches today, I was 
informed by a light fearing citizen of Caemlyn there was 
an odd man at the Golden Bowl inn.  Upon arrival I discovered 
a man *desc of Cordell* with eyes that appeared to yellow at 
table. To my surprise there was also a man who claimed to be 
a Child of the Light *desc Leon* going by the name of Child 
Atreides. Child Atreides and I approached this man who had 
obviously given his soul to the Dark one, thus accounting for 
his yellow eyes.  When requested to come with us, the man 
refused. Upon questioning him there, I found his name to be 
Lord Cordell Fenevall, of House Damodred.  Since I am personally 
not familiar with House Damodred, I can neither attest to the 
validity of his claim or not.  Since Child Atreides or I could 
not be sure, we requested again that he come with us.  However 
at that moment, another man entered *desc Asin*, it is at this 
point that I have very sad news to report.  Child Atreides broke 
ranks and ran.  I do understand what I write here, and I swear 
under the light and with my salvation to the light, that this 
is true.  Since, I have never seen such cowardliness in our 
ranks before
I do not believe this Child Atreides was truly 
one of our own.  After the false Child of the Light ran, my 
options were very limited, because it became very apparent that 
this man *desc Asin* would aid Lord Fenevall.  I viewed it more 
important to deliver the news, of both men, and the traitors 
Child (if he truly be a Child of the Light at all). 

The light illumine us all,
*signed*
Child Malik


</text>
