      <heading>Sun Sep  1 (Masema)     :: &amp;WNEW GEQ!&amp;n</heading>
      <slot>34</slot>
      <level>211</level>
      <author>0</author>
      <date>0</date>
      <text>Okay peeps.  I went ahead and did Angua a small (hah!)
favor and redid the entirity of your GUILD EQ.  Basically
I streamlined the stats and changed the descs into stuff
that isn't so hard on the eyes (although this GEQ is also
toolable).

Couple things, anyone with old GEQ will notice that I
changed the short descs (IE: when you type &quot;eq&quot;) so
that they alert you to come ask for new GEQ.  Not
only did I change the short descs, I also flagged all
the old stuff !SAVE (except for the Gcontainers, calm
down) mostly due to the fact that there has been
some problems with old CotL GEQ floating around where
it shouldn't be (like on mobs, etc.).  Oh yeah, I also
removed the stats (aside from the capacity of the
Gcontainers that is).

As I said, the GEQ is toolable, but Angua is the one
who will tell you whether or not she really wants it
altered.  In fact, she may even end up redoing a lot
of the descs I wrote so that they correspond with ranks
like they should-- like she wants it.

I wrote a fairly complete Ghelp file detailing the GEQ as
it is now.  Please check it out: GHELP 1 NEW_GEQ.

Direct any complaints to me, for this was all my doing.

If you need a new GEQ set, just ask me or Angua or
even Arif!

That is all.

Masema
PS- This was mostly done out of sheer frustration with
the previous set of GEQ... Ugh.  The stats.. the utter
confusion!  I'm still going through the healing process.
I'll be alright, just give it time.  *mutters about all caps
on short descs under his breath*
</text>
