      <heading>Mon Sep 16 (Fredrik)    :: New toy for you.</heading>
      <slot>36</slot>
      <level>210</level>
      <author>0</author>
      <date>0</date>
      <text>I have, as an experiment, swapped your call mobs (those that
appear when you type reinforce) for retainers.
This means that reinforce no longer exists as a command, but is only
used to check whether you can get the retainers. If you don't have the
skill, you can't, obviously.
These &quot;guild retainers&quot; are bought at the same place as all the rest;
oval, s, 2e.
They don't cost anything to buy and they don't impose any rent either;
they're totally for free.
In addition to this, they have IC as well as OOC power (just as much
as the old call mobs), so you can individualize these henchmen and
give them eq etc just like any other retainer.
There is one limit to this however; you cannot get more than four of 
these &quot;special type retainers&quot;. This to avoid _too_ much cheating.
Also, Arif and Angua determine whether _all_ the rules pertaining to
this new toy. If they say you can't play with them even though you have
the skill, you cant't, period.
Confused? Ask Arif and Angua. If they can't answer, _wait_ until they get
some word from the immies, don't go behind their backs to get quick
answers.
Remember, this is a trial run. If all goes well, all call mobs will be
swapped for equivalent-strength retainers. If not, they won't...which applies
to your darling call mobs as well. Mess this up and you can kiss these
free retainers goodbye.

./Fredrik
</text>
    </message>
