      <text>The ranks of a soldier are:

&amp;rLord Captain
&amp;RSecond Captain
&amp;yLieutenant
&amp;YUnder-Lieutenant
&amp;wHundredman
&amp;cFirst Bannermen 
&amp;CBannermen
&amp;mFirst Squadman 
&amp;MSquadman
&amp;gFile Leader
&amp;bSoldier
&amp;nRecruit


&amp;nFor a player to achieve the following enlisted ranks they must completed the objectives listed next to the rank.  Thus if a recruit wanted to become a First bannerman he must gain every rank below, completing all the listed tasks (meaning a total of 54 RP logs, and 9 recommendations).

&amp;bSoldier&amp;n: 4 logged RP sessions and one recommendation from group A, B or C
&amp;gFile Leader&amp;n: 6 logged RP sessions and one recommendation from group A, B or C
&amp;MSquadman&amp;n: 8 logged RP sessions and one recommendation from group A,B or C 
&amp;mFirst Squadman&amp;n: 10 logged RP sessions and two recommendations from group A, B or C
&amp;cBannerman&amp;n: 12 logged RP sessions and two recommendations from group B or C
&amp;CFirst Bannerman&amp;n: 14 logged RP sessions and two recommendations from: B or C

Advancement in the officer ranks:
&amp;wHundredman&amp;n: &amp;Y*&amp;n
&amp;yUnder Lieutenant&amp;n:  &amp;Y*&amp;n
&amp;YLieutenat&amp;n: &amp;Y*&amp;n
&amp;RSecond Captain&amp;n:  &amp;Y*&amp;n
&amp;rLord Captain&amp;n:  &amp;Y*&amp;n

Key
Group A:  Senior enlisted (Squadman or Bannerman)
Group B:  Junior officer (Hundredman or Lieutenant rank)
Group C:  Senior Officer (Captain or above)
&amp;Y*&amp;n: Advancement to any officer rank will only be given to a soldier if their BG supports such a promotion, as well as other factors including but not limited to time in the Children, over all RP, IC interview for an officer rank plus an OOC interview.
